3. 
Application Layer: External layer where the user can see the data of the DB
-> can be relational

Implementation layer: Internal / Conceptional layer where the content of the DB can be modified, defining all 
connections between tables 
-> should be relational

Physical Layer: The physical storage of the data

4. 
DML 

Data Manipulation Language -> used by moderators of the DB to modify the content of the DB
-> queue and modify tables and relations

DDL

Data Definition Language
-> used by the moderators of the DB to create tables and relations, aswell as the attributes contained by it

5. 
A Primary Key (PK) is an attribute or an attribute combination which identifies each tupel of a table uniquely
- it must be unique for every tupel / row
- it must not be NULL
- it should be simple

