9. 
A Foreign key is a relation between to tables, allowing one to map one Data to multiple other sets of data, without
putting multiple values in one attribute.

10. 

When setting up relations, you can setup two ways to handle deletions:

    Restrict:   This restricts the deletion completely of the foreign key completely.
    Cascade:    This causes the deletion to cascade into all related values, causing the deletion of a connected keys to the foreign key.

    The standard is Restrict.

